    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, you can use `--TerminalInteractiveShell.editing_mode=vi` or set `c.TerminalInteractiveShell.editing_mode='vi'` in your configuration option. \r\n\r\nIt is not perfect, but ressemble VI.\r\n\r\nYou can switch dynamically with something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [1]: ip= get_ipython()\r\nIn [2]: ip.editing_mode\r\nOut[2]: 'emacs'\r\nIn [3]: ip.editing_mode='vi'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is no mode indicator, I'm sure there is an issue somewhere about that. If you figure it out feel free to send PR, or at least pointer. And/Or send updates to the docs. \r\n\r\nIn general `ipython --help-all` and search through the output can be useful to figure out these can of things."
  },
